@page "/privacy-policy"

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - PdfToolStack</PageTitle>

<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for PdfToolStack, including file processing, temporary file deletion, account data, analytics, and support contact information." />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://pdftoolstack.com/privacy-policy" />
</HeadContent>

<main class="trust-page">
    <section class="trust-hero">
        <div>
            <span class="trust-eyebrow">Privacy Policy</span>
            <h1>Practical privacy for document workflows.</h1>
            <p>
                This policy explains what PdfToolStack collects, how uploaded files are handled,
                and how to contact us about privacy questions.
            </p>
        </div>
        <aside class="trust-summary-card">
            <span>Support contact</span>
            <a href="mailto:admin@pdftoolstack.com">admin@pdftoolstack.com</a>
            <small>Effective date: May 20, 2026</small>
        </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="trust-grid">
        <article class="trust-card">
            <h2>File handling</h2>
            <p>
                Files you upload are used to perform the tool action you request, such as
                compression, conversion, signing, redaction, or AI-assisted review.
            </p>
            <p>
                Uploaded and generated files are intended for temporary processing only. We do
                not intentionally keep permanent copies of your uploaded documents, and files are
                designed to be deleted automatically after processing, typically within 1 hour.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="trust-card">
            <h2>Information we may collect</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Basic usage data, such as pages visited and tool events.</li>
                <li>Account information if you sign in, such as authentication identifiers.</li>
                <li>Subscription status and billing metadata needed to provide paid features.</li>
                <li>Technical logs used for reliability, security, abuse prevention, and debugging.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                We do not need your file name, file contents, extracted text, or payment card
                details for analytics events.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="trust-card">
            <h2>PDF processing disclaimer</h2>
            <p>
                PDF processing can be imperfect. Complex layouts, scans, fonts, images, signatures,
                form fields, password protection, or corrupted files may affect output quality.
                You are responsible for reviewing downloaded results before relying on them.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="trust-card">
            <h2>AI-assisted tools</h2>
            <p>
                Some tools may use third-party AI or document-processing services to perform the
                requested workflow. AI output is informational and may be incomplete or incorrect.
                It is not legal, financial, tax, medical, or professional advice.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="trust-card">
            <h2>Payments and subscriptions</h2>
            <p>
                Paid features may be handled through a third-party payment processor. Payment card
                details should be entered only into the secure checkout flow, not sent by email.
            </p>
            <p>
                We may receive limited billing metadata from the processor, such as plan status,
                checkout status, renewal information, or customer identifiers needed to provide
                account access and support. We do not receive full card numbers.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="trust-card">
            <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
            <p>
                PdfToolStack may use essential cookies for sign-in, preferences, security, and
                consent choices. Analytics may be used to understand page performance and improve
                tools. Advertising cookies are used only if advertising features are enabled and
                consent or applicable settings allow them.
            </p>
            <p>
                See the <a class="trust-inline-link" href="/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a> for
                more detail about cookie categories and user controls.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="trust-card">
            <h2>Your choices</h2>
            <p>
                You can contact us to ask privacy questions, request account help, or raise a
                document-handling concern. Please do not email sensitive documents unless we ask
                for them and you are comfortable sharing them.
            </p>
            <a class="trust-inline-link" href="mailto:admin@pdftoolstack.com">admin@pdftoolstack.com</a>
        </article>
    </section>
</main>
